{
  "texts": [
    "Ainu is a critically endangered family of dialects from from Northern Japan without any native writing script.",
    "6.2.3 Dialect MT in Shared Tasks.",
    "Given that most dialects are spoken and not written, the IWSLT workshop, which focuses on spoken language translation, has been conducting shared tasks on dialects under the banner of low-resource MT.",
    "The 2022 6 and 2023 7 workshops featured dialectal speech translation, with resources for text-text as well as speech-text translation.",
    "The focus, as is typically the case, is on dialects of Arabic like Tunisian, Egyptian and Moroccan."
  ]
}